WEBVTT

00:12.263 --> 00:15.266
[Camille] No one knows
exactly who coined the term

00:15.266 --> 00:17.268
"strong Black woman"

00:17.268 --> 00:19.729
or even exactly
when the term originated.

00:19.729 --> 00:23.482
What we do know is the trope
is uniquely American

00:23.482 --> 00:26.861
and has been germane from
slavery to the present day.

00:26.861 --> 00:29.155
In comparison
to white femininity,

00:29.155 --> 00:30.656
which is valued for beauty,

00:30.656 --> 00:31.824
vulnerability,

00:31.824 --> 00:33.409
and maternal softness,

00:33.409 --> 00:36.370
Black women have been
valued for their labor,

00:36.370 --> 00:39.665
both literally
and figuratively.

00:39.665 --> 00:43.085
A strong Black woman
suppresses her emotions,

00:43.085 --> 00:44.795
never letting anyone
see her sweat.

00:44.795 --> 00:46.338
She is ambitious,

00:46.338 --> 00:48.090
but still makes time
to be supportive,

00:48.090 --> 00:51.051
even carrying her mate,
her friends,

00:51.051 --> 00:53.304
and her family when necessary.

00:53.304 --> 00:56.182
Being labeled
a strong Black woman

00:56.182 --> 00:58.392
is a rite of passage.

00:58.392 --> 01:00.561
She is resilient, independent,

01:00.561 --> 01:02.313
and capable.

01:02.313 --> 01:04.064
[sighs]

01:04.064 --> 01:05.608
But what if she isn't?

01:05.608 --> 01:08.986
It's been four fucking hours
since the doctor has been here.

01:08.986 --> 01:11.197
Do you know what I could do
in four hours?

01:11.197 --> 01:12.740
We could have binge-watched
Roots by now.

01:12.740 --> 01:14.700
- You ever seen Roots?
- Mm-mm.

01:14.700 --> 01:16.285
Not even a remake with T.I.?

01:16.285 --> 01:17.369
Definitely not.

01:17.369 --> 01:19.580
Tch, Black people kill me
not Blacking.

01:19.580 --> 01:21.081
You seen it?

01:21.081 --> 01:23.292
Nah, but it's still on my DVR.

01:23.292 --> 01:24.960
- [both laugh]
- Bitch.

01:24.960 --> 01:27.087
Oh, fuck.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.006
Yo, whatever it is,

01:29.006 --> 01:31.050
it needs to happen quick.

01:31.050 --> 01:33.093
I have my flight to AfroTech
in the morning.

01:33.093 --> 01:35.346
You are not getting on
a plane in this condition.

01:35.346 --> 01:37.264
Oh, I am not missing AfroTech.

01:37.264 --> 01:39.809
It is the Mecca
for Black techies.

01:39.809 --> 01:42.603
And there's gonna be mad,
blerd chicks to holla at,

01:42.603 --> 01:43.771
and did we forget...

01:43.771 --> 01:45.689
[both] Your girl
is a keynote speaker.

01:45.689 --> 01:48.275
Mm-hmm, but if you do not
make your health your focus,

01:48.275 --> 01:50.694
I'm gonna be the keynote
speaker at your funeral.

01:50.694 --> 01:53.197
See, this is why I don't
tell people when I'm sick,

01:53.197 --> 01:54.365
because it becomes a thing.

01:54.365 --> 01:55.699
And then the next thing
you know,

01:55.699 --> 01:57.409
everybody's acting like
you got six weeks to live

01:57.409 --> 01:58.869
when it's just
a damn runny nose.

01:58.869 --> 02:01.664
A runny nose does not
cause you to pass out

02:01.664 --> 02:03.749
on a disgusting subway floor.

02:03.749 --> 02:05.459
By the way, we should probably
have them check you

02:05.459 --> 02:09.088
for hepatitis A and B and C.

02:09.088 --> 02:10.881
- Is there a D?
- Whatever.

02:10.881 --> 02:12.675
My point is,
I don't like to be treated

02:12.675 --> 02:14.343
like I'm weak sauce.

02:14.343 --> 02:16.345
Or petted like a damn dog.

02:16.345 --> 02:17.805
Quinn, you didn't
tell anybody, did you?

02:17.805 --> 02:19.849
Oh, my God, for the
millionth time, I didn't.

02:19.849 --> 02:21.934
Good, I don't need
Camille in here

02:21.934 --> 02:23.143
tracing stomach pain

02:23.143 --> 02:25.855
back to the Middle Passage
or some shit.

02:25.855 --> 02:27.064
And Angie would be up in here

02:27.064 --> 02:29.650
stealing hospital supplies
as reparations.

02:29.650 --> 02:32.778
Oh, God, the doctor said
he would be right back.

02:32.778 --> 02:34.446
I'm gonna fucking lose it.

02:34.446 --> 02:36.949
See, this is why my family
doesn't fuck with doctors.

02:36.949 --> 02:38.659
They don't treat us anyway.

02:38.659 --> 02:40.953
The most they do
is experiment like Tuskegee.

02:40.953 --> 02:42.997
- The Relf Sisters.
- Mississippi Appendectomy.

02:42.997 --> 02:44.373
- Henrietta Lacks.

02:44.373 --> 02:46.000
Well, hello, dear.

02:46.000 --> 02:47.668
So you're anemic.

02:47.668 --> 02:48.711
Let's get you
a blood transfusion,

02:48.711 --> 02:50.087
get your numbers back up.

02:50.087 --> 02:52.464
Okay, and what about
her back and her pelvic pain?

02:52.464 --> 02:55.384
Ah, that's just Aunt Flo
being a tough houseguest.

02:55.384 --> 02:56.760
When your cycle's over
in a few days,

02:56.760 --> 02:58.512
the pain will subside.

02:58.512 --> 03:00.639
What if it's been
more than a few days?

03:00.639 --> 03:02.892
I've been on my period
for 11 days now.

03:02.892 --> 03:04.101
What?

03:04.101 --> 03:05.352
[Doctor] Well,
every woman is different.

03:05.352 --> 03:07.605
Well, as a woman,
I would say that 11 days

03:07.605 --> 03:09.273
deserves a far more
aggressive approach

03:09.273 --> 03:10.900
to her diagnosis than Aunt Flo.

03:10.900 --> 03:13.861
And the Tylenol ain't
cutting it for the pain.

03:13.861 --> 03:15.654
Ah, so you're here for drugs?

03:15.654 --> 03:18.616
I'm here because I passed out
on a damn subway.

03:18.616 --> 03:20.034
We have a very
strict policy against

03:20.034 --> 03:21.911
prescribing opioids
in this community.

03:21.911 --> 03:24.246
Well, from what I hear,
this community

03:24.246 --> 03:26.081
isn't the one that you need
to be worried about.

03:26.081 --> 03:28.334
Now, my friend
is in serious pain.

03:28.334 --> 03:30.169
You have not done
any ultrasounds,

03:30.169 --> 03:31.670
- Any checks, any...
[Doctor] As a doctor,

03:31.670 --> 03:34.757
I have her bloodwork and that
tells me all I need to know.

03:34.757 --> 03:36.592
Have you tried relaxing,
meditation?

03:36.592 --> 03:38.886
This could all just be
stress in your head.

03:38.886 --> 03:41.555
I'll have the nurse get started
on your blood transfusion.

03:41.555 --> 03:42.598
Ooh.

03:42.598 --> 03:44.391
O negative, universal donor.

03:44.391 --> 03:46.894
You should consider getting on
a regular donation schedule.

03:46.894 --> 03:48.354
A lot of people could
really use your help.

03:48.354 --> 03:50.314
I'm sorry,
did you just tell her

03:50.314 --> 03:52.066
that she needed
a blood transfusion

03:52.066 --> 03:54.151
and then asked for her shit
back in the same breath?

03:54.151 --> 03:56.111
I can see we're a little upset.

03:56.111 --> 03:57.112
I'm gonna go.

03:57.112 --> 03:59.531
The nurse will be by.

03:59.531 --> 04:01.617
We're upset?

04:01.617 --> 04:02.993
Shit.

04:02.993 --> 04:04.828
Thank God you can go home
after this transfusion,

04:04.828 --> 04:07.456
but 11 days, Tye?

04:07.456 --> 04:10.292
Why you ain't tell me?

04:10.292 --> 04:11.919
I don't wanna lose you.

04:11.919 --> 04:14.088
Lose me, Quinn?

04:14.088 --> 04:16.423
Wow.

04:16.423 --> 04:19.385
Wow.
Great work, Camille.

04:19.385 --> 04:21.679
Of course it is, Nora.

04:21.679 --> 04:23.681
And that's "Dr. Parks."

04:23.681 --> 04:26.517
Well, since Dr. Pruitt
asked you to assist me,

04:26.517 --> 04:28.686
I thought we were
more colleagues.

04:28.686 --> 04:31.438
And remind me,
where did you get your PhD?

04:31.438 --> 04:34.108
Like I said, Dr. Parks.
Thanks.

04:34.108 --> 04:36.944
Do you know
a Dr. Amina Reynolds?

04:36.944 --> 04:38.153
I know of her.

04:38.153 --> 04:39.405
Well, I met her earlier today

04:39.405 --> 04:41.865
after she interviewed
with Dr. Pruitt.

04:41.865 --> 04:43.617
She seems really nice.
Who knows?

04:43.617 --> 04:46.787
Maybe next year
I'll get to take her class.

04:46.787 --> 04:50.290
She was interviewing for the
associate professor's position?

04:50.290 --> 04:53.293
Not sure, but probably.

04:53.293 --> 04:55.170
Well, have a good night,
Dr. Parks.

04:59.133 --> 05:00.259
[sighs]

05:00.259 --> 05:01.760
[whispers] Fuck.

05:01.760 --> 05:04.805
[phone ringing]

05:07.599 --> 05:09.643
Hey, hey, hey, beautiful,
I was just about to text you.

05:09.643 --> 05:11.603
I'm thinking Zoma
or Pisticci tonight.

05:11.603 --> 05:13.605
[Camille] I'm sorry, babe,
I can't do dinner tonight.

05:13.605 --> 05:15.482
I just found out that
Dr. Pruitt is interviewing

05:15.482 --> 05:17.693
outside candidates for the
associate professor position.

05:17.693 --> 05:19.153
[Jameson]
For tenure track?

05:19.153 --> 05:21.697
- I thought that was all you.
[Camille] So did I.

05:21.697 --> 05:24.867
Now, I need to update my CV,
gather my materials,

05:24.867 --> 05:26.076
and compose
my mission statement

05:26.076 --> 05:28.370
to present it to Dr. Pruitt,
like, yesterday,

05:28.370 --> 05:29.830
and you know
it's gotta be tight.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.248
[Jameson] And it will be.
Look, you got this.

05:31.248 --> 05:33.042
And if, you know,
if we have time,

05:33.042 --> 05:34.460
we can meet up later
for a nightcap.

05:34.460 --> 05:37.004
Okay, wait, you wanna hear
something funny?

05:37.004 --> 05:39.590
So in middle school,
I used to think that

05:39.590 --> 05:42.718
nightcap was slang for condom

05:42.718 --> 05:45.095
'cause you put it, like,
on your head, get it?

05:45.095 --> 05:48.265
I do get it, um, but don't
tell anybody else that.

05:48.265 --> 05:51.435
- [line beeps]
- Hold on.

05:51.435 --> 05:53.395
Oh, shit, um,
I need to get this.

05:53.395 --> 05:55.105
It's my therapist,
but I will see you later.

05:55.105 --> 05:57.524
[Jameson] All right.

05:57.524 --> 05:59.485
Rebecca, hi.

05:59.485 --> 06:01.737
I am so sorry that I missed
our session earlier.

06:01.737 --> 06:02.988
I got caught up at work and...

06:02.988 --> 06:04.198
[Rebecca]
This is the third session

06:04.198 --> 06:05.824
- you've missed this month.
- Yeah.

06:05.824 --> 06:07.659
[Rebecca] If you don't wish
to continue your therapy...

06:07.659 --> 06:10.162
No, no, no.
I do, I do.

06:10.162 --> 06:12.289
Do you have anything tomorrow?
Please?

06:12.289 --> 06:15.417
I will work with
whatever you have available.

06:15.417 --> 06:16.960
[Rebecca]30.
- Okay.

06:16.960 --> 06:20.464
30.
I will be there.

06:20.464 --> 06:23.467
Yes.

06:23.467 --> 06:24.843
[quietly]
Yes, okay.

06:24.843 --> 06:26.261
[mellow music]

06:26.261 --> 06:28.847
[exhales]
Mission statement.

06:28.847 --> 06:30.307
[exhales]

06:30.307 --> 06:32.976
[singer]

07:34.037 --> 07:36.832
[upbeat piano melody]

07:57.102 --> 07:58.770
Yeah, pretty much
from the age of six,

07:58.770 --> 08:01.106
I could tell you that the
traffic light and peanut butter

08:01.106 --> 08:03.025
were both invented
by Black men.

08:03.025 --> 08:05.777
Also how about
that Harriet Tubman?

09:29.194 --> 09:30.570
[all] Yeah!

09:30.570 --> 09:31.780
Ugh, seriously?

09:31.780 --> 09:34.449
[Mark] And, scene.
Kate, you okay?

09:34.449 --> 09:36.034
This marking tape
is so ghetto.

09:36.034 --> 09:37.369
It's like barely
stuck to the floor.

09:37.369 --> 09:39.162
[Mark] Hey, okay.
We'll take care of it.

09:39.162 --> 09:40.872
No, Mark.
It's not just the tape.

09:40.872 --> 09:43.125
Like, what is up with
this whole ghetto set design?

09:43.125 --> 09:45.002
Is she pronouncing
"Get Out" weird,

09:45.002 --> 09:46.586
or calling everything ghetto?

09:46.586 --> 09:48.672
Kate, to be honest, you were
a little late on your mark.

09:48.672 --> 09:51.633
Yeah, no shit, Mark,
but how am I supposed to tell?

09:51.633 --> 09:53.260
I'm so over this
ghetto production.

09:53.260 --> 09:55.554
Kay, why do you keep
saying "ghetto?"

09:55.554 --> 09:58.307
- What?
- You keep saying "ghetto."

09:58.307 --> 10:01.059
- What do you mean by that?
- [laughs]

10:01.059 --> 10:02.769
Are you calling me racist?

10:02.769 --> 10:05.772
Depends on how you answer
the question.

10:05.772 --> 10:07.232
[scoffs]

10:07.232 --> 10:09.818
- Oh, my God.
- White girls gonna white.

10:09.818 --> 10:11.236
Mark, can we move on
to a number

10:11.236 --> 10:14.197
featuring those of us
without a ghetto work ethic?

10:14.197 --> 10:15.699
- Kate!
- Good.

10:15.699 --> 10:17.367
Those of us
in the "Sunken Place" number,

10:17.367 --> 10:18.535
front and center.

10:18.535 --> 10:20.871
Ain't nobody got time
for that today.

10:24.249 --> 10:26.626
[grunts]
Mm.

10:26.626 --> 10:27.961
This is the second time
I've stayed the night

10:27.961 --> 10:29.379
at your house,

10:29.379 --> 10:33.300
and the second time you've
stayed up all night working.

10:33.300 --> 10:35.135
I'm sorry.
Sorry.

10:35.135 --> 10:37.304
There's just never enough time
to get everything done,

10:37.304 --> 10:39.639
but I promise
that I will make time for us.

10:39.639 --> 10:41.016
Don't apologize.

10:41.016 --> 10:42.684
Most people just
talk about going hard,

10:42.684 --> 10:45.228
but you, you actually do it.
[laughs]

10:45.228 --> 10:48.315
Yeah, well,
while y'all sleep, I grind.

10:48.315 --> 10:49.941
I love that.

10:49.941 --> 10:53.695
Yeah, but even the grind
can't outrun time.

10:53.695 --> 10:55.614
I think I'm gonna have
to cancel my class so that

10:55.614 --> 10:57.574
I can get everything done for
this meeting with Dr. Pruitt.

10:57.574 --> 11:00.410
Cancel your class? You might
as well cancel your tenure.

11:00.410 --> 11:01.453
Cam, how are you going to show

11:01.453 --> 11:02.996
you can be
a tenure track professor

11:02.996 --> 11:04.956
if you cancel class every time
you need a few extra minutes?

11:04.956 --> 11:06.666
Damn, you're right.
You're right.

11:06.666 --> 11:08.585
I know it's tough.

11:08.585 --> 11:11.922
But remember pressure is
what turns coal into diamonds,

11:11.922 --> 11:14.716
and you, my dear,
are a diamond.

11:14.716 --> 11:16.676
You know, I'm so used
to the men in my life

11:16.676 --> 11:20.138
always saying that I take
everything so seriously.

11:20.138 --> 11:21.723
It's kind of dope
having someone

11:21.723 --> 11:23.767
that pushes me to be my best.

11:23.767 --> 11:25.685
I mean, come on,
as the great poets once said,

11:25.685 --> 11:28.688
"You and I gots to do
for you and I."

11:28.688 --> 11:30.107
Exactly.

11:30.107 --> 11:32.901
[singer]

11:32.901 --> 11:34.444
[upbeat music]

11:34.444 --> 11:35.695
[Quinn]
Hey, Mom.

11:35.695 --> 11:39.199
I need you to take in
this dress 2 inches.

11:39.199 --> 11:41.201
Three weeks on keto.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.620
- You look good.
- I look outstanding.

11:43.620 --> 11:45.997
Maybe you should try keto.

11:45.997 --> 11:47.374
Mm.

11:47.374 --> 11:48.917
Busy as usual.

11:48.917 --> 11:53.338
Actually,
I am designing a wedding dress.

11:53.338 --> 11:55.966
For $25,000.

11:55.966 --> 11:59.469
[Patricia]
I love this color, lilac.

11:59.469 --> 12:01.555
And she's recommending me
to all of her friends.

12:01.555 --> 12:03.932
[Patricia] What you call
that pink color?

12:03.932 --> 12:05.392
- "Mohv"?
- Mauve.

12:05.392 --> 12:07.894
And after getting the deposit,

12:07.894 --> 12:09.771
the store is officially
in the black

12:09.771 --> 12:11.815
for the very first time.

12:11.815 --> 12:13.650
[gasps]

12:13.650 --> 12:16.987
I think you're gonna have
to come in 3 inches.

12:16.987 --> 12:19.823
Oh, keto, where have you been
all my life?

12:19.823 --> 12:22.951
Uh, Mom, did you hear
what I just said?

12:22.951 --> 12:24.327
Yes, but talk to me

12:24.327 --> 12:26.163
when you can go
more than 30 days

12:26.163 --> 12:29.124
without asking me and your
father to keep the lights on.

12:29.124 --> 12:31.835
Mom, all businesses operate
at a deficit in the beginning.

12:31.835 --> 12:33.587
But yours remain there--

12:33.587 --> 12:35.380
the juice bar, the spa.

12:35.380 --> 12:37.174
Well, this is different.

12:37.174 --> 12:39.342
This is what I was supposed
to be doing all along.

12:39.342 --> 12:42.762
Mom, I've been trying
really hard to turn a profit.

12:42.762 --> 12:44.639
The least you could do
is acknowledge that.

12:44.639 --> 12:46.475
Acknowledged.

12:46.475 --> 12:49.186
And you should acknowledge
that one wedding dress

12:49.186 --> 12:51.938
does not
a successful business make.

12:51.938 --> 12:53.899
What size do you think
I am now?

12:53.899 --> 12:55.734
I don't know.
Six?

12:55.734 --> 12:59.529
I am 10 cauliflower pizzas
away from a four.

12:59.529 --> 13:02.908
Then you'll be my size.

13:02.908 --> 13:05.660
Interesting, considering

13:05.660 --> 13:08.079
I have had two children.

13:13.084 --> 13:15.962
[singer]

13:24.471 --> 13:25.805
[clears throat]

13:28.183 --> 13:30.644
Kate is asking
for a little more time

13:30.644 --> 13:32.062
before she can rehearse.

13:32.062 --> 13:35.273
See, this that 53% of white
women bullshit right here.

13:35.273 --> 13:36.566
We better still
get paid for this.

13:36.566 --> 13:39.528
- Okay?
- I want us all to remember

13:39.528 --> 13:42.239
that we are a family
when we're all on this stage.

13:42.239 --> 13:45.158
When one of us makes an
insensitive comment to another,

13:45.158 --> 13:46.701
it hurts the production
as a whole.

13:46.701 --> 13:48.620
Mm, say that.

13:48.620 --> 13:50.413
We have to be careful
with our words.

13:50.413 --> 13:53.750
That's right.
Watch your mouths up in here.

13:53.750 --> 13:55.585
...because words can hurt.

13:55.585 --> 13:57.504
I mean, I wasn't really hurt.

13:57.504 --> 13:58.964
More like, "What the fuck?"

13:58.964 --> 14:00.257
But I get what you mean.

14:00.257 --> 14:01.967
Shit wasn't cool.

14:01.967 --> 14:03.385
- Angie.
- I ain't like it.

14:03.385 --> 14:05.512
Can I see you for a moment?

14:05.512 --> 14:06.972
Sure.

14:08.223 --> 14:09.683
Okay, good luck.

14:11.268 --> 14:13.895
I need you
to apologize to Kate.

14:13.895 --> 14:15.855
Ex-fucking-scuse me?

14:15.855 --> 14:17.774
She should be apologizing
to me.

14:17.774 --> 14:19.442
Shit, to all of us.

14:19.442 --> 14:21.987
She says something fucked up
nearly every day.

14:21.987 --> 14:23.697
Look, she's really upset

14:23.697 --> 14:24.948
and she won't come back
to rehearsal

14:24.948 --> 14:26.116
until you apologize.

14:26.116 --> 14:28.159
I guess you need to cast
another Rose then.

14:28.159 --> 14:30.829
I know some talented white
girls who know how to act.

14:30.829 --> 14:31.997
You want me to make some calls?

14:31.997 --> 14:34.165
- Angie, come on.
- Why?

14:34.165 --> 14:36.001
Why am I the one
who has to come on?

14:36.001 --> 14:38.670
She over here making
some offensive-ass comments

14:38.670 --> 14:40.213
and somehow she's the victim.

14:40.213 --> 14:41.965
Come the fuck on
with that shit.

14:41.965 --> 14:44.384
Angie, you basically said
that she was racist,

14:44.384 --> 14:45.594
and we both know
that isn't true.

14:45.594 --> 14:48.054
One, if it looks like
a microaggression

14:48.054 --> 14:49.472
and talks like
a microaggression,

